# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — neklam/nvim
# =============================================================================

# ── lazy.nvim plugin store ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# lazy.nvim downloads plugins here at runtime. Never commit these —
# they are re-downloaded automatically on any new machine.
/lazy/

# ── Mason binaries ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Mason installs LSP servers, formatters, and linters here.
# These are large platform-specific binaries; Mason reinstalls them on demand.
/mason/

# ── lazy-lock.json ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# UNCOMMENT the line below ONLY if you do NOT want to pin plugin versions.
# By default we commit lazy-lock.json so that all machines use identical
# plugin versions. This is the recommended approach for a personal config.
# /lazy-lock.json

# ── Machine-specific / personal overrides ────────────────────────────────────
# Create this file locally for anything that shouldn't be public:
# workspace paths, API keys, machine-specific LSP settings, etc.
lua/plugins/local.lua

# ── Neovim runtime state ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are generated at runtime and vary per machine.
/swap/
/backup/
/undo/
/log/
/view/

# ── Neovim shada (shared data) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Search history, marks, registers — personal and machine-specific.
*.shada
*.shada.tmp.*

# ── OS noise ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── Editor noise ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.swp
*.swo
*~
\#*\#
\n# Vim native packages (not managed by lazy.nvim)\npack/
